<subSubSection pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="93.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,152,179]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Discussion:</emphasis>
This species is known from a single female specimen, collected on Mt. Moffat in Carnarvon National park, 
<collectingRegion box="[289,425,189,215]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Queensland</collectingRegion>
. Although no male has been collected, a fragment of the DNA barcode was successfully obtained from the 
<typeStatus box="[354,455,225,251]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">holotype</typeStatus>
, so if a male is collected in the future it can be confidently matched to the 
<typeStatus box="[1272,1370,225,251]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">holotype</typeStatus>
using DNA evidence. The barcode data extracted from the 
<typeStatus box="[747,845,261,287]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">holotype</typeStatus>
is publicly available on the BOLD website (Process ID: SYRAU381-18), as detailed above in the Materials and methods section.
</paragraph>
